1
00:00:46,881 --> 00:00:51,010
<i>Kim Hee-ae</i>

2
00:00:54,221 --> 00:00:58,184
<i>Ko Asung</i>

3
00:01:00,728 --> 00:01:04,774
<i>Kim You-jeong, Kim Hyang-gi</i>

4
00:01:07,443 --> 00:01:11,781
<i>Yu Ah-in, Sung Dong-il</i>

5
00:01:20,081 --> 00:01:21,749
It's not ironed

6
00:01:22,208 --> 00:01:24,794
It'll wrinkle after an hour anyway

7
00:01:25,836 --> 00:01:28,005
But it's nice to wear
a neatly pressed shirt

8
00:01:28,005 --> 00:01:29,381
Give me three minutes

9
00:01:29,465 --> 00:01:30,758
This is just fine

10
00:01:54,907 --> 00:01:56,784
There's no soup?

11
00:01:56,909 --> 00:01:59,787
Don't complain
or we'll switch to cereal

12
00:02:01,997 --> 00:02:03,874
The eggs look perfect

13
00:02:03,999 --> 00:02:05,709
Aren't you a sweetheart?

14
00:02:07,128 --> 00:02:09,463
Man-ji, learn from your sister

15
00:02:09,630 --> 00:02:11,048
I take after you, mom

16
00:02:12,550 --> 00:02:13,467
<i>Directed by Lee Han</i>

17
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:15,803
Directed by Lee <i>Han</i>
You're not gonna have that, then?

18
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:16,929
No

19
00:02:17,805 --> 00:02:19,056
Yay

20
00:02:28,190 --> 00:02:29,233
Mom

21
00:02:29,316 --> 00:02:30,401
Yeah?

22
00:02:30,734 --> 00:02:32,319
Can you buy me an MP3 player?

23
00:02:34,572 --> 00:02:36,866
What for?

24
00:02:37,324 --> 00:02:42,913
Just that... everyone else
has one and I don't

25
00:02:43,831 --> 00:02:45,374
What kind of a silly reason is that?

26
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:49,086
Everyone has one
so, you must have one too?

27
00:02:49,378 --> 00:02:51,463
Make it an early birthday present

28
00:02:51,839 --> 00:02:54,758
Months in advance?

29
00:02:55,259 --> 00:02:56,510
Just get one for her

30
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:57,928
Who said I wouldn't?

31
00:02:59,096 --> 00:03:01,932
How about next month?

32
00:03:02,349 --> 00:03:04,268
We have to renew the lease
this month

33
00:03:05,394 --> 00:03:09,190
Just listen from your phone
Who uses MP3 player these days?

34
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,152
Wait up, Man-ji

35
00:03:13,194 --> 00:03:14,612
I'm late

36
00:03:18,908 --> 00:03:20,242
Sorry, honey...

37
00:03:20,242 --> 00:03:23,370
can you put the dishes
in the sink?

38
00:03:28,334 --> 00:03:29,376
Man-ji

39
00:03:37,259 --> 00:03:41,764
Come and have a taste
Tofu is buy one get one free

40
00:03:41,847 --> 00:03:45,100
Would you like to sample
some tofu, ma'am?

41
00:03:46,894 --> 00:03:49,063
Dumplings!

42
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:50,356
Hey, Cheon-ji
What's up?

43
00:03:50,356 --> 00:03:52,650
<i>Can you knit a hat for me
with my yarn?</i>

44
00:03:52,650 --> 00:03:56,278
First an MP3 player
and now, a woolly hat?

45
00:03:56,737 --> 00:03:57,905
One for stew, please

46
00:03:57,988 --> 00:04:00,741
Honey, I'm busy
Can we talk later?

47
00:04:00,741 --> 00:04:01,909
How about some dumplings, ma'am?

48
00:04:01,909 --> 00:04:03,577
Sorry about that

49
00:04:04,286 --> 00:04:08,207
It's organic and
buy one get one free today

50
00:04:08,249 --> 00:04:10,334
- Thank you
- Have a good day

51
00:04:12,169 --> 00:04:14,880
Dumplings, ma'am?

52
00:04:14,922 --> 00:04:20,761
Roll up your skirt
It's really bothering me

53
00:04:21,262 --> 00:04:25,933
Your's looks as if
it's about to explode

54
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:29,687
Dress like a dork
if you like getting picked on

55
00:04:29,895 --> 00:04:33,232
Just shut up and decide
which snack parlor

56
00:04:33,816 --> 00:04:36,819
Of course your diet
was going to last

57
00:04:39,029 --> 00:04:43,158
Look at the middle-schoolers
So sweet...

58
00:04:43,993 --> 00:04:48,163
That teacher loves making
the girls hug each... pervert!

59
00:04:48,414 --> 00:04:50,082
Yeah, that'll help them make up

60
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:52,668
She's Mi-ra and Cheon-ji's
home room teacher

61
00:04:53,002 --> 00:04:55,587
Mi-ra...?
Oh, your sister!

62
00:04:56,422 --> 00:04:58,173
She and Cheon-ji
are in the same class?

63
00:04:58,465 --> 00:04:59,967
Didn't Cheon-ji tell you?

64
00:05:00,634 --> 00:05:02,803
Mi-ra talks about her sometimes

65
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:04,972
What does she say?

66
00:05:05,472 --> 00:05:07,182
I don't think they're that close

67
00:05:07,474 --> 00:05:09,393
So, have we decided?

68
00:05:09,977 --> 00:05:10,894
Attal

69
00:05:10,978 --> 00:05:12,479
Okay

70
00:05:17,609 --> 00:05:18,485
What?

71
00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:21,071
<i>Was it MP3 player
that Cheon-ji wanted?</i>

72
00:05:21,322 --> 00:05:22,990
There are so many different kinds

73
00:05:23,032 --> 00:05:25,784
You said you needed to
save up for security deposit

74
00:05:25,951 --> 00:05:29,163
It's an MP3 player
It's not gonna make us homeless

75
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:32,791
Can you ask her
which model she wants?

76
00:05:35,461 --> 00:05:37,796
There was something about her tone

77
00:05:38,130 --> 00:05:40,466
<i>She never asks for anything</i>

78
00:05:40,466 --> 00:05:42,009
I don't know... I gotta go

79
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:39,358
<i>Cheon-ji died</i>

80
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:52,454
<i>My baby sister who was pressing
her shirt to perfection all morning</i>

81
00:06:53,747 --> 00:06:56,166
<i>took her own life</i>

82
00:06:57,084 --> 00:06:59,294
<i>without leaving a note</i>

83
00:07:05,342 --> 00:07:06,677
Cheon-ji's dad

84
00:07:08,095 --> 00:07:10,848
Don't ask her why
if you see her

85
00:07:14,017 --> 00:07:15,769
Just give her a hug

86
00:07:19,189 --> 00:07:20,524
<i>Bitch...</i>

87
00:07:22,901 --> 00:07:24,445
Good bye, baby

88
00:07:38,667 --> 00:07:41,295
<i>Nine years after burying dad</i>

89
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:44,131
<i>mom had to bury her little girl</i>

90
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:56,768
<i>ELEGANT LIES</i>

91
00:08:07,488 --> 00:08:11,074
I've only just buried my baby

92
00:08:11,366 --> 00:08:15,913
How dare you talk about
my daughter that way

93
00:08:16,330 --> 00:08:20,584
when you could've just
asked me to move out

94
00:08:24,296 --> 00:08:25,672
Have a good life,
you rotten hag!

95
00:08:29,801 --> 00:08:31,845
Get us out of here
as fast as you can

96
00:08:36,391 --> 00:08:38,268
Why didn't you leave behind
the things we don't want?

97
00:08:39,269 --> 00:08:40,938
The hag tells me to
take everything

98
00:08:53,659 --> 00:08:58,038
It feels so weird
to be just you and me

99
00:09:03,794 --> 00:09:05,462
Thank you

100
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:13,720
Hello!
We're moving into 103

101
00:09:19,268 --> 00:09:22,271
No room for privacy

102
00:09:23,438 --> 00:09:27,401
Doesn't it smell like
old public toilet in here?

103
00:09:28,402 --> 00:09:30,279
Didn't you check the apartment
when you signed the contract?

104
00:09:31,029 --> 00:09:33,824
I signed when I heard
it was Chowon Apartment

105
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:39,371
Where do I sleep?

106
00:09:39,663 --> 00:09:41,415
We can sleep here together

107
00:09:41,665 --> 00:09:42,916
I don't think so

108
00:09:43,584 --> 00:09:45,460
Then, you take the living room

109
00:09:54,261 --> 00:09:58,140
We'll have to get rid of your desk
There's no room

110
00:09:58,432 --> 00:10:00,100
You don't want me to study?

111
00:10:02,769 --> 00:10:08,317
I'll get a small foldable table

112
00:10:08,734 --> 00:10:10,485
I'll just use Cheon-ji's

113
00:10:13,822 --> 00:10:15,157
It's okay

114
00:10:16,325 --> 00:10:17,534
Alright

115
00:10:19,202 --> 00:10:20,662
I'll put this in the balcony

116
00:10:20,704 --> 00:10:23,206
Let's clean it up first

117
00:10:32,299 --> 00:10:33,759
What is this smell?

118
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:37,137
Look out for a hidden
secret toilet

119
00:10:46,772 --> 00:10:48,857
Can you get the garbage bag?

120
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:52,235
- Oh my God!
- What?

121
00:10:52,611 --> 00:10:53,528
What?

122
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:58,950
- What is it, mom?
- Rats

123
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:01,244
- Oh, no... catch them
- You do it

124
00:11:01,244 --> 00:11:02,829
No, you do it, mom

125
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:07,542
Who the hell are you?

126
00:11:07,626 --> 00:11:09,753
I live next door

127
00:11:10,337 --> 00:11:11,672
Are you a rocker?

128
00:11:13,757 --> 00:11:16,426
No, I'm studying for
the civil service exams

129
00:11:19,596 --> 00:11:23,767
That is one precise middle parting

130
00:11:25,435 --> 00:11:27,020
I appreciate the beauty of balance

131
00:11:28,105 --> 00:11:29,314
Freak...

132
00:11:29,690 --> 00:11:31,400
So, you're a man?

133
00:11:32,067 --> 00:11:33,568
What's going on inside?

134
00:11:34,778 --> 00:11:35,862
Rats...

135
00:11:36,279 --> 00:11:38,490
Yeah, it's a big problem
in this building

136
00:11:38,490 --> 00:11:41,952
They're swarming in the box
in the balcony

137
00:11:42,828 --> 00:11:46,373
Can I call 911 for this?

138
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:50,961
Why don't you let me handle this?

139
00:11:58,051 --> 00:12:00,887
There is a dust pan
in the balcony

140
00:12:03,014 --> 00:12:04,558
Which box is it?

141
00:12:04,558 --> 00:12:08,562
The moldy one
in the furnace closet

142
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:14,234
I'll close this first
in case they try to escape

143
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:21,032
He's kind of dependable

144
00:12:42,763 --> 00:12:44,681
What's wrong?

145
00:12:48,977 --> 00:12:52,606
It's too big... I'm sorry

146
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:55,108
Gives me the creeps

147
00:12:55,442 --> 00:12:57,110
So much for his big words

148
00:12:57,944 --> 00:13:01,865
Next time I see him,
I'll give him pigtails

149
00:13:01,948 --> 00:13:04,409
He almost broke that door

150
00:13:04,951 --> 00:13:06,495
Dependable?

151
00:13:07,454 --> 00:13:08,622
Did I say that?

152
00:13:08,955 --> 00:13:10,415
Shall we call the security?

153
00:13:10,874 --> 00:13:14,044
He won't lift a finger for free

154
00:13:17,589 --> 00:13:19,633
I couldn't find the big one

155
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:21,635
- Argh
- Hey!

156
00:13:22,552 --> 00:13:24,387
You can't just catch the small one

157
00:13:24,471 --> 00:13:26,139
We'll see if it comes back

158
00:13:28,016 --> 00:13:31,561
I gave you 10 dollars
for that tiny little one?

159
00:13:31,645 --> 00:13:35,148
So, there might still be
a rat in there?

160
00:13:35,482 --> 00:13:38,193
Shall I get some bug spray?

161
00:13:38,652 --> 00:13:40,070
Like that's gonna kill a rat

162
00:13:40,946 --> 00:13:43,990
It'll kill the ticks
on rat's skin

163
00:13:44,366 --> 00:13:47,118
I have a feeling that
I'll run away soon

164
00:13:47,577 --> 00:13:50,539
I have a feeling I'll be
taking more shifts at work

165
00:13:51,665 --> 00:13:54,835
- Let me help you with other things
- No, thank you

166
00:13:54,918 --> 00:13:58,046
That one
We need to throw that out

167
00:14:00,507 --> 00:14:02,467
You can't let a stranger
in our house

168
00:14:02,509 --> 00:14:04,344
There's nothing for him to take

169
00:14:06,721 --> 00:14:08,515
What's your name?

170
00:14:09,349 --> 00:14:10,642
Lee Man-ji

171
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:12,227
Lee Man-ji

172
00:14:14,187 --> 00:14:16,231
It's an easy name to make fun of

173
00:14:19,985 --> 00:14:21,528
I'm Chu Sang-bak

174
00:14:21,695 --> 00:14:27,325
Chusang Park or Chu Sangbak?

175
00:14:27,492 --> 00:14:30,120
It's Chu Sang-bak

176
00:14:31,705 --> 00:14:35,208
No charge for the glass
The board is three dollars

177
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:38,378
The dresser, also three dollars
So, six dollars in total

178
00:14:38,420 --> 00:14:42,007
The board and the dresser are a set
You can't charge them separately

179
00:14:42,007 --> 00:14:46,636
It's the size that matters
Even as a set, it's six dollars

180
00:14:46,887 --> 00:14:48,138
Hey

181
00:14:48,430 --> 00:14:51,224
You charged me five dollars
for a dresser similar to this one

182
00:14:51,516 --> 00:14:54,853
You see?
I don't decide this as I want

183
00:14:54,853 --> 00:14:56,730
There are guidelines to follow

184
00:14:58,565 --> 00:15:00,025
Five dollars

185
00:15:00,025 --> 00:15:02,110
Oh, come on

186
00:15:03,069 --> 00:15:05,030
Isn't that Cheon-ji's friend?

187
00:15:05,906 --> 00:15:07,991
It's Hwa-yeon
Bosingak owner's daughter

188
00:15:13,121 --> 00:15:14,915
So, that's that

189
00:15:16,499 --> 00:15:19,336
I'm hungry
Let's get something to eat, Man-ji

190
00:15:24,257 --> 00:15:25,967
Can we have a word?

191
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:27,135
What about?

192
00:15:27,469 --> 00:15:31,139
You can't charge people differently
as you please

193
00:15:31,139 --> 00:15:34,434
The economy isn't
what it used to me

194
00:15:34,434 --> 00:15:35,852
It was two weeks ago

195
00:15:36,978 --> 00:15:38,730
Okay

196
00:15:40,315 --> 00:15:43,485
Then, let's just settle for this

197
00:15:46,821 --> 00:15:48,865
I'm only doing this because
you're like a son to me

198
00:15:52,535 --> 00:15:53,828
Hello

199
00:15:56,081 --> 00:15:59,793
We just moved here. I guess
we'll be seeing each other around

200
00:16:00,251 --> 00:16:02,212
Right...

201
00:16:03,505 --> 00:16:04,756
I'm back

202
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:08,468
We'll have two black bean noodles
with a sweet and sour pork

203
00:16:08,802 --> 00:16:10,595
- Two black noodles and one pork
- We can't eat all that

204
00:16:10,595 --> 00:16:12,305
We're not three people

205
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:17,227
Of course, we can
We're gonna need that much energy

206
00:16:17,852 --> 00:16:21,147
- Can we cancel the pork?
- No, we'll have it

207
00:16:26,945 --> 00:16:29,906
You gotta eat black bean noodles
when you move

208
00:16:30,365 --> 00:16:34,869
I'm sick of moving
How come you never bought a house?

209
00:16:36,371 --> 00:16:39,708
By the time I save some money
the house price soars out of reach

210
00:16:40,041 --> 00:16:43,670
and you want to go to cram schools
to get good grades

211
00:16:43,837 --> 00:16:45,005
What choice do I have?

212
00:16:45,171 --> 00:16:46,506
Alright, I take it back

213
00:16:47,674 --> 00:16:51,428
New to the neighborhood?
We also deliver

214
00:16:51,678 --> 00:16:54,014
We'll pop around
We live next door

215
00:16:54,681 --> 00:16:58,810
How kind of you!
Enjoy your noodles

216
00:17:02,522 --> 00:17:06,526
Study hard for mom, okay?

217
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:09,279
They say 'unlucky in marriage,
poor luck with children too'

218
00:17:09,529 --> 00:17:10,864
Prove them wrong

219
00:17:10,905 --> 00:17:13,867
With what luck
could I possibly achieve that?

220
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:17,037
You talk back constantly

221
00:17:18,288 --> 00:17:24,252
It's good. We are the ones
that talk... I like that

222
00:17:26,421 --> 00:17:29,507
Mom, stop being so dramatic
You're making me uncomfortable

223
00:17:29,883 --> 00:17:31,217
Let's just stay the way
we used to be

224
00:17:31,301 --> 00:17:33,928
My daughter's nagging
gives me energy. It's good

225
00:17:52,405 --> 00:17:57,702
Let's get this straight, moron
I didn't end it because you're a bum

226
00:17:59,454 --> 00:18:05,960
Don't make the unemployment
problem your excuse

227
00:18:06,377 --> 00:18:09,047
You just hate working

228
00:18:10,215 --> 00:18:11,758
Don't wait for my call, you damn...

229
00:18:17,472 --> 00:18:21,184
Bastard... Why would I
tell you about moving?

230
00:18:22,936 --> 00:18:24,145
What?

231
00:18:25,271 --> 00:18:27,023
No, don't wait for me there

232
00:18:32,570 --> 00:18:37,575
Stop being pathetic
You've got kids to look after

233
00:18:39,994 --> 00:18:41,287
What?

234
00:18:43,957 --> 00:18:45,333
Cheon-ji's mom?

235
00:18:48,753 --> 00:18:50,922
Don't you dare mention
my daughter's name

236
00:19:08,106 --> 00:19:09,607
Good night

237
00:19:10,817 --> 00:19:11,985
Night

238
00:19:19,492 --> 00:19:23,538
Why did she do it?

239
00:19:24,956 --> 00:19:26,624
Do you know anything about it?

240
00:19:47,729 --> 00:19:48,855
What are you doing?

241
00:19:50,857 --> 00:19:53,109
I had borrowed it from Cheon-ji

242
00:19:54,861 --> 00:19:56,321
When?

243
00:19:56,362 --> 00:19:58,239
Three months ago maybe

244
00:19:58,531 --> 00:19:59,490
Three months?

245
00:19:59,490 --> 00:20:01,034
She never asked for it back

246
00:20:01,117 --> 00:20:03,912
So, you didn't bother returning it?

247
00:20:03,912 --> 00:20:06,497
I thought she'd come get it
if she needed it back

248
00:20:07,457 --> 00:20:10,084
So, she has to come to you
to kindly ask for it back

249
00:20:10,084 --> 00:20:12,170
It was only a gym uniform

250
00:20:12,212 --> 00:20:14,881
Of course
What about Cheon-ji

251
00:20:14,881 --> 00:20:17,508
who would've been terrified
what you might do if she say no?

252
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:19,636
Why the fuck did
she have to kill herself?

253
00:20:19,636 --> 00:20:20,553
What?

254
00:20:22,347 --> 00:20:23,431
What did you say?

255
00:20:26,309 --> 00:20:30,730
Hwa-yeon gave it to me
saying it would fit me

256
00:20:30,813 --> 00:20:33,858
Are you friends with Hwa-yeon?

257
00:20:34,025 --> 00:20:36,236
We got close after she invited me
to her birthday party

258
00:20:36,402 --> 00:20:39,155
- What about Cheon-ji?
- She's not my style

259
00:20:41,950 --> 00:20:44,202
She was best friends with Hwa-yeon

260
00:20:44,285 --> 00:20:47,038
But I only know Hwa-yeon
not Cheon-ji

261
00:21:06,099 --> 00:21:08,017
I'm Cheon-ji's sister

262
00:21:11,312 --> 00:21:13,231
The scent is so thick

263
00:21:13,273 --> 00:21:14,774
Hi

264
00:21:19,862 --> 00:21:22,407
Can we have a word after school?

265
00:21:23,283 --> 00:21:24,492
Cheonji

266
00:21:26,577 --> 00:21:28,329
Hey

267
00:21:29,831 --> 00:21:31,249
Are you her sister?

268
00:21:31,291 --> 00:21:32,333
Yeah

269
00:21:32,583 --> 00:21:35,795
Hi!
I'm Cheon-ji's friend, Hwa-yeon

270
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:37,297
Hwa-yeon

271
00:21:38,047 --> 00:21:42,635
It's so great to finally meet you
Why don't you buy me a pork cutlet?

272
00:21:43,761 --> 00:21:45,138
You don't have to

273
00:21:47,890 --> 00:21:51,519
You two are so different

274
00:21:53,062 --> 00:21:55,565
They say opposites attract

275
00:21:58,818 --> 00:22:00,945
I don't have enough
for pork cutlet but...

276
00:22:02,155 --> 00:22:04,949
Can we get two rice cakes
in chili sauce?

277
00:22:05,992 --> 00:22:07,327
Thank you

278
00:22:10,038 --> 00:22:11,122
Excuse me for a moment?

279
00:22:16,502 --> 00:22:18,004
I'm going

280
00:22:19,672 --> 00:22:21,215
I'm on my way

281
00:22:21,424 --> 00:22:23,468
- Here's your rice cake
- Thank you

282
00:22:23,468 --> 00:22:24,510
Hwa-yeon

283
00:22:24,844 --> 00:22:25,928
What are you doing?

284
00:22:26,179 --> 00:22:28,056
I met Cheon-ji's sister

285
00:22:28,639 --> 00:22:31,684
I asked her to get pork cutlet
but she's buying me rice cake instead

286
00:22:36,439 --> 00:22:37,732
So, what do you think?

287
00:22:43,071 --> 00:22:44,655
She's cute

288
00:22:50,411 --> 00:22:52,872
I felt bad about not buying you
that pork cutlet

289
00:22:57,377 --> 00:22:58,753
Thank you

290
00:23:00,922 --> 00:23:05,218
I heard you and Cheon-ji were best friends
You must be upset

291
00:23:05,802 --> 00:23:09,889
I've known her since elementary school
but we weren't best friends

292
00:23:10,848 --> 00:23:15,478
I don't know what the girls
said about the day she died

293
00:23:16,604 --> 00:23:20,566
but Cheon-ji seemed quite upset
during the presentation

294
00:23:22,527 --> 00:23:25,154
What are the evils of prejudice?

295
00:23:25,405 --> 00:23:29,409
Especially when it is
maliciously disseminated

296
00:23:29,867 --> 00:23:32,370
Let's look at some common ways
in which prejudice can be fostered

297
00:23:32,787 --> 00:23:37,041
One, slander disguised
as a compliment

298
00:23:37,417 --> 00:23:40,837
People react more sensitively
to smaller points than the basis

299
00:23:41,129 --> 00:23:42,130
Example:

300
00:23:42,422 --> 00:23:45,883
'She always gets good grades
but she's actually quite dumb'

301
00:23:46,217 --> 00:23:50,555
Basis, good grades,
point, dumb

302
00:23:52,557 --> 00:23:56,060
Your cruel words can kill

303
00:23:57,437 --> 00:24:02,108
Are you a murderer in the making?

304
00:24:06,696 --> 00:24:07,989
Thank you

305
00:24:12,076 --> 00:24:16,205
What an interesting presentation!

306
00:24:16,831 --> 00:24:20,501
But 'a murdererin the making'?
Don't you think you took too far?

307
00:24:21,169 --> 00:24:23,296
Should I have said
a 'confirmed murderer' instead?

308
00:24:25,923 --> 00:24:29,135
I'm sorry, Cheon-ji
I'm really sorry, okay?

309
00:24:29,302 --> 00:24:30,428
Let me go

310
00:24:35,141 --> 00:24:36,809
Cheon-ji, I'm sorry

311
00:24:37,643 --> 00:24:39,729
Why do you always apologize to her?

312
00:24:40,188 --> 00:24:41,314
What's the matter with her?

313
00:24:41,355 --> 00:24:43,024
It's not like you ever
did anything to her

314
00:24:43,024 --> 00:24:45,067
- What a self-absorbed bitch!
- Totally

315
00:24:45,902 --> 00:24:50,865
She was going through something
terrible and I never knew it

316
00:24:52,325 --> 00:24:54,911
So, I told myself that
I'll be a better friend for her

317
00:24:55,077 --> 00:24:58,623
I only asked you if you were upset
and that's a pretty long answer

318
00:25:01,626 --> 00:25:03,753
I thought you might want to know

319
00:25:06,130 --> 00:25:08,841
Does everyone have MP3 players?

320
00:25:10,510 --> 00:25:14,347
Probably, although I can't
be bother to carry mine around

321
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:15,640
Why?

322
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:18,809
Cheon-ji was asking for
an MP3 player before she died

323
00:25:19,185 --> 00:25:20,978
I wondered if you knew
anything about it

324
00:25:26,859 --> 00:25:31,197
We were going to exchange gifts
for our birthdays

325
00:25:32,823 --> 00:25:34,367
Was it your birthday?

326
00:25:35,785 --> 00:25:37,328
Among close friends,

327
00:25:37,328 --> 00:25:40,456
we pick out the presents
and give each other before the birthdays

328
00:25:41,290 --> 00:25:42,750
An early present...

329
00:25:42,833 --> 00:25:45,545
an MP3 player
that you rarely use, no less?

330
00:25:46,796 --> 00:25:47,964
That doesn't seem right

331
00:25:48,047 --> 00:25:51,467
There are cheap ones, too
For 20 dollars or less

332
00:25:52,385 --> 00:25:57,223
Stupid girl... troubled over an MP3
when there are cheaper ones, too

333
00:25:59,809 --> 00:26:01,102
Why aren't you eating?

334
00:26:01,644 --> 00:26:02,728
I am

335
00:26:06,315 --> 00:26:08,901
Are you close with Soo-gyeong?

336
00:26:10,945 --> 00:26:14,824
She's a delinquent
She's a friend of a friend's

337
00:26:17,034 --> 00:26:21,414
but she seemed close with Cheon-ji
They lend each other gym uniforms

338
00:26:22,957 --> 00:26:27,253
They used to lend each other
gym uniforms?

339
00:26:27,628 --> 00:26:29,213
Well, yeah...

340
00:26:39,390 --> 00:26:42,977
I didn't know you moved
to my neighborhood

341
00:26:43,603 --> 00:26:47,732
I saw you yesterday
I thought you saw me, too

342
00:26:48,107 --> 00:26:50,735
I would've said hi
if I did

343
00:26:53,863 --> 00:26:56,741
These apartments are so old,
aren't they?

344
00:26:57,241 --> 00:27:00,286
I lived here all my life
I'm so sick of this place

345
00:27:00,870 --> 00:27:05,374
but my parents won't go anywhere
unless the restaurant shuts down

346
00:27:06,500 --> 00:27:09,670
Well, our black bean noodle
is quite famous in this area

347
00:27:10,129 --> 00:27:11,297
You

348
00:27:13,674 --> 00:27:15,968
You can't stand the silence,
can you?

349
00:27:18,095 --> 00:27:19,889
It makes you nervous

350
00:27:20,139 --> 00:27:23,017
So, this is what she meant

351
00:27:24,644 --> 00:27:29,815
I just didn't want to be rude
since you treated me

352
00:27:29,899 --> 00:27:31,776
Cheon-ji said that you were cool

353
00:27:31,984 --> 00:27:33,486
You really are

354
00:27:34,403 --> 00:27:38,324
I think she once said that
it's hard to talk to you

355
00:27:39,158 --> 00:27:41,243
Then again, I'm not sure

356
00:27:46,666 --> 00:27:50,670
There's nothing cool about
being cool-headed about your sister's death

357
00:27:51,671 --> 00:27:56,759
But I guess it's okay
to talk about it now

358
00:27:58,094 --> 00:27:59,970
I think I'll look for
her suicide note

359
00:28:01,263 --> 00:28:02,723
I thought she didn't leave
any note

360
00:28:02,973 --> 00:28:05,768
Why wouldn't she?
I just haven't looked yet

361
00:28:06,352 --> 00:28:08,854
Maybe I'll start soon

362
00:28:10,564 --> 00:28:11,899
or not

363
00:28:18,197 --> 00:28:19,615
<i>Declaration of Friendship</i>

364
00:28:19,615 --> 00:28:20,700
Cheonji

365
00:28:24,036 --> 00:28:26,664
Are you still mad at me?

366
00:28:27,331 --> 00:28:30,000
I already told everyone
that it was a joke

367
00:28:31,377 --> 00:28:33,879
Didn't I correct myself about

368
00:28:33,879 --> 00:28:35,840
Cheon-ji being bullied
in elementary school?

369
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:41,220
Are you still mad about that?

370
00:28:42,138 --> 00:28:45,891
No, I never heard that
It's not about that

371
00:28:45,975 --> 00:28:48,310
Alright!
I'm sorry anyway, okay?

372
00:28:48,394 --> 00:28:49,311
Come here

373
00:28:51,731 --> 00:28:53,858
Let's sign a
Declaration of Friendship

374
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:56,235
Sign here

375
00:29:02,867 --> 00:29:06,412
This certified that Lee Cheon-ji
and Kim Hwa-yeon are best friends

376
00:29:10,875 --> 00:29:13,794
Hey, that MP3 player you're
getting me for my birthday

377
00:29:13,878 --> 00:29:17,339
Give it to me to commemorate
becoming best friends

378
00:29:17,590 --> 00:29:20,593
I'll give you the digital camera

379
00:29:39,820 --> 00:29:42,740
Mi-ran, tell me what your sister
told you about Cheon-ji

380
00:29:43,324 --> 00:29:44,825
About Cheon-ji and Hwa-yeon

381
00:29:48,954 --> 00:29:50,956
Come and have a taste

382
00:29:51,624 --> 00:29:53,959
It's specially cooked in
low temperature for extra flavor

383
00:29:54,251 --> 00:29:54,960
It's really good

384
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:58,005
There's no additives
or preservatives...

385
00:30:04,595 --> 00:30:05,471
Noodle, quickly

386
00:30:05,554 --> 00:30:06,472
With sauce?

387
00:30:06,555 --> 00:30:08,724
- No, in soup
- Coming right up

388
00:30:08,724 --> 00:30:09,809
Give me a large one

389
00:30:09,892 --> 00:30:11,310
- A large one
- Double portion

390
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:16,607
The noodle's cooked just right

391
00:30:29,161 --> 00:30:32,540
What's the matter, 'Tofu'?

392
00:30:37,503 --> 00:30:40,005
I just buried my baby

393
00:30:47,847 --> 00:30:51,976
and I'm sitting here stuffing
myself with an extra large noodle

394
00:30:52,768 --> 00:30:54,645
trying to live

395
00:30:59,066 --> 00:31:01,527
She's watching you from above
Go on, eat

396
00:31:19,420 --> 00:31:21,380
This is Cheon-ji's stuff

397
00:31:22,339 --> 00:31:25,593
You live in the same building
as her family?

398
00:31:25,968 --> 00:31:27,845
Her sister asked you to
bring this over for her

399
00:31:28,971 --> 00:31:29,972
Okay

400
00:31:50,784 --> 00:31:56,498
It's true that we were best friends
but she made me feel suffocating

401
00:31:57,249 --> 00:32:01,295
She would nitpick over
every little thing

402
00:32:02,421 --> 00:32:04,006
Put the box in there

403
00:32:05,424 --> 00:32:08,427
I was the only friend she had

404
00:32:08,510 --> 00:32:10,804
Wasn't it because of you
that she only had you?

405
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:14,934
Look, I just felt bad about denying
she was my best friend, that's all

406
00:32:15,267 --> 00:32:19,188
Don't try to provoke me
You won't get anywhere

407
00:32:19,813 --> 00:32:21,357
Thanks for bringing it over

408
00:32:25,653 --> 00:32:27,613
- Your youngest got over cold?
- Yes

409
00:32:27,613 --> 00:32:31,283
Hey, I know these are
promotional give aways

410
00:32:35,412 --> 00:32:36,747
- Thanks
- Sure

411
00:32:39,833 --> 00:32:41,001
What's he doing here?

412
00:32:41,210 --> 00:32:43,003
He's enjoying the free buffet

413
00:32:43,504 --> 00:32:45,005
I think he came to see you

414
00:32:45,965 --> 00:32:48,467
That pathetic asshole

415
00:32:49,468 --> 00:32:52,054
If I saved up every penny
I spent on him...

416
00:32:52,304 --> 00:32:54,807
Who can I blame, but myself?

417
00:32:56,809 --> 00:32:57,935
Hello

418
00:32:59,979 --> 00:33:01,355
Oh, sorry

419
00:33:01,772 --> 00:33:03,941
Your hair...

420
00:33:05,859 --> 00:33:07,111
Can I get three blocks of tofu?

421
00:33:07,319 --> 00:33:09,947
Are you throwing a party?

422
00:33:09,989 --> 00:33:11,365
I'm making dumplings

423
00:33:11,573 --> 00:33:12,825
And, you need three blocks?

424
00:33:13,158 --> 00:33:16,620
I make a fridge load at a time
and have them for meals

425
00:33:16,787 --> 00:33:18,372
If you're making dumplings

426
00:33:18,831 --> 00:33:22,001
get the cheaper ones over there
These are pricy

427
00:33:24,003 --> 00:33:26,714
Oh... thank you

428
00:33:39,601 --> 00:33:40,686
Do you know him?

429
00:33:40,853 --> 00:33:42,021
He lives next door

430
00:33:42,271 --> 00:33:45,858
A man who makes
his own dumplings

431
00:33:47,026 --> 00:33:48,569
Do you know what shampoo he uses?

432
00:33:49,695 --> 00:33:51,113
How would I know that?

433
00:33:51,196 --> 00:33:52,990
He has a beautiful silky hair

434
00:33:54,992 --> 00:33:56,910
Can you ask him for me?

435
00:34:00,247 --> 00:34:01,457
Should I get a transplant?

436
00:34:04,460 --> 00:34:06,086
Dear me... I'm sorry

437
00:34:06,211 --> 00:34:09,840
Can we have a word?

438
00:34:10,507 --> 00:34:12,760
Piss off
before I call the security

439
00:34:12,885 --> 00:34:14,053
You want me to?

440
00:34:15,471 --> 00:34:20,851
I just want to talk
Or I'll come everyday

441
00:34:21,268 --> 00:34:22,728
It'll only be a second

442
00:34:23,187 --> 00:34:27,733
I'm sorry for everything
Let's start over

443
00:34:27,733 --> 00:34:31,528
You've done nothing wrong
I just don't like you anymore

444
00:34:31,570 --> 00:34:33,405
No, come on
Forgive me

445
00:34:33,572 --> 00:34:35,741
- Let me go
- I won't

446
00:34:35,741 --> 00:34:36,909
For crying out loud!

447
00:34:38,160 --> 00:34:39,286
Jeez...

448
00:34:42,039 --> 00:34:44,458
I miss you so much
that I can't do anything

449
00:34:44,458 --> 00:34:45,918
Get off of me

450
00:34:47,711 --> 00:34:48,587
What the heck?

451
00:34:52,591 --> 00:34:54,593
Have you lost your mind?

452
00:34:55,969 --> 00:34:57,346
Leave her alone

453
00:35:01,683 --> 00:35:02,768
What the hell?

454
00:35:04,561 --> 00:35:05,437
You crazy bastard...

455
00:35:06,730 --> 00:35:07,773
You crazy bitch!

456
00:35:07,773 --> 00:35:10,484
What's your problem, bitch?

457
00:35:10,484 --> 00:35:12,152
Stop it

458
00:35:12,152 --> 00:35:13,654
Bitch

459
00:35:13,987 --> 00:35:14,988
Here

460
00:35:15,114 --> 00:35:17,241
Come on

461
00:35:20,619 --> 00:35:21,995
Over here

462
00:35:21,995 --> 00:35:24,498
Don't ignore my calls, okay?

463
00:35:32,965 --> 00:35:35,008
I was about to strike back

464
00:35:35,092 --> 00:35:38,262
You were letting him
beat you down all he wants

465
00:35:40,639 --> 00:35:42,724
I used to be bullied back
in high school

466
00:35:42,724 --> 00:35:44,351
so, I learned boxing

467
00:35:45,978 --> 00:35:49,314
If you cover your face and torso,
it really doesn't hurt

468
00:35:50,399 --> 00:35:51,817
Are you sure you're okay?

469
00:35:51,817 --> 00:35:52,734
Absolutely

470
00:35:54,862 --> 00:35:57,865
Can I touch your hair
for a second?

471
00:36:03,120 --> 00:36:05,539
No? Oh, thank you

472
00:36:15,132 --> 00:36:16,049
That's her

473
00:36:18,093 --> 00:36:20,387
That girl in Class III
died because of her

474
00:36:31,899 --> 00:36:34,735
<i>Switching seats</i>

475
00:36:46,580 --> 00:36:51,919
I can't believe we're doing this
in middle school

476
00:36:53,879 --> 00:36:56,089
You said Cheon-ji's father
killed himself

477
00:36:56,381 --> 00:36:57,633
When did say that?

478
00:36:57,966 --> 00:36:59,218
At your birthday party

479
00:37:00,552 --> 00:37:01,929
Did I?

480
00:37:01,929 --> 00:37:04,389
My sister is friends with Man-ji

481
00:37:04,890 --> 00:37:08,018
She asked me about
you and Cheon-ji

482
00:37:10,062 --> 00:37:12,940
She hit the ceiling when
I told her about the father's suicide

483
00:37:13,232 --> 00:37:15,234
She said he was
killed in an accident

484
00:37:16,401 --> 00:37:19,321
I don't remember saying that...

485
00:37:19,655 --> 00:37:22,449
But it's true
You said that

486
00:37:22,866 --> 00:37:24,952
You said that Cheon-ji is
somber because of that

487
00:37:25,744 --> 00:37:27,746
Fine!
Tell Man-ji everything

488
00:37:28,330 --> 00:37:33,126
I see so much of her everyday
that I'm growing fond of her

489
00:37:40,884 --> 00:37:43,136
You moved to my school
in fifth grade

490
00:37:43,220 --> 00:37:45,347
I always wanted
to be friends with you

491
00:37:45,681 --> 00:37:49,851
Picking out your next target?

492
00:37:51,186 --> 00:37:52,938
That hurts

493
00:37:54,606 --> 00:37:58,694
I heard that your specialty
was the new girls

494
00:37:58,777 --> 00:38:02,990
They warned me to be careful
or I'll end up like Cheon-ji

495
00:38:04,116 --> 00:38:08,495
What nonsense!
Cheon-ji and I were best friends

496
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:10,956
Do friends do exactly
as they're told?

497
00:38:11,039 --> 00:38:13,000
I asked her favors and
she did them for me

498
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:16,295
You call them favors?
They were orders and coercion

499
00:38:17,462 --> 00:38:20,132
I'm the only one that
actually hung out with her

500
00:38:20,590 --> 00:38:24,094
Did any of you even look at her?

501
00:38:32,561 --> 00:38:36,982
How convenient for you is it
that she never fought back?

502
00:38:37,065 --> 00:38:39,651
How could you be so relentless
about bullying her?

503
00:38:39,985 --> 00:38:41,611
I would've killed myself, too

504
00:38:43,905 --> 00:38:48,035
Wow, you're playing a hero?

505
00:38:48,660 --> 00:38:51,496
Whether you like it or not,
I was her only friend

506
00:38:51,496 --> 00:38:54,541
Alright,
so I didn't hang out with her

507
00:38:54,833 --> 00:38:57,419
but at least,
I didn't manipulate her

508
00:38:57,627 --> 00:38:59,379
Do you have a conscience?

509
00:38:59,713 --> 00:39:02,007
To tell you the truth,
Cheon-ji was hard to get close to

510
00:39:02,341 --> 00:39:06,261
but do you know
what your nickname is?

511
00:39:06,928 --> 00:39:10,140
'Free wallet'

512
00:39:10,515 --> 00:39:13,435
You always buy things for us
and pay for karaoke

513
00:39:13,977 --> 00:39:16,188
Popcorn's always on you
when we go to the movies

514
00:39:22,819 --> 00:39:26,239
You didn't say a word
when she was around

515
00:39:27,532 --> 00:39:29,826
Now I'm the only bitch?

516
00:39:31,745 --> 00:39:36,917
I'm gonna tell Man-ji that
Cheon-ji was an outcast

517
00:39:38,001 --> 00:39:41,171
I have the conversation history
of our group chat room as proof

518
00:39:42,214 --> 00:39:45,884
You're all accomplices

519
00:39:58,397 --> 00:39:59,815
That's mine

520
00:40:02,776 --> 00:40:03,985
Get out of here

521
00:40:08,615 --> 00:40:10,409
- Cheon-ji is coming, too?
- Yeah

522
00:40:10,492 --> 00:40:12,411
Why do you care about her?

523
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:15,831
I feel sorry for her

524
00:40:16,081 --> 00:40:18,959
